## Closing summary

The overall finding is that CCBNY has a strong governance and compliance model foundation, but the evidence does not yet fully demonstrate a sustainable DFS 504 data lineage control environment. The highest-risk themes are end-to-end lineage, CDE ownership, completeness/accuracy evidence, reconciliation coverage, sanctions screening coverage, change impact controls, and certification evidence. These should be prioritized because they directly affect the Branch’s ability to support the required annual DFS 504 compliance finding and to demonstrate that transaction monitoring and filtering programs operate on complete and accurate data.

